data.title: Converse Ready, Set Get Lost: Hunters "Deadbeat" Live
data.description:
Hunters, one of the most talked about bands of a busy festival season in NYC, kicked off our Ready, Set: Get Lost series with an incredible performance on the roof of Factory Studios in Brooklyn. The BK band tore through a rendition of "Deadbeat" on a gorgeous day in the city with the NYC skyline as their backdrop.

Thanks to Guitar Center, Gretsch Drums and Zildjian Cymbals.

data.title: Converse Ready, Set Get Lost: Kilo Kish "Navy (MeLo X Remix)" Live
data.description:
The name Kilo Kish was on the tip of everyone's tongue last week in NYC, as the Orlando-bred songstress brought her carefree, whimsical style to venues all over Brooklyn and Manhattan. We caught up with her at 1896 building in Bushwick, as part of our Ready, Set Get Lost series, where she closed the evening with a stunning performance of her single Navy (MeLo X Remix) - complete with visuals and some crazy shadows. 

Thanks to Guitar Center, Gretsch Drums, and Zildjian cymbals.

data.title: Converse Ready, Set Get Lost: Mood Rings "Pathos Y Lagrimas" Live
data.description: Mood Rings made the long drive north for an insanely busy week of shows, and left NYC as one of it's most buzzed about bands. They joined us in a dilapidated building in an undisclosed location in NYC as part of our Ready, Set Get Lost series for a gorgeous rendition of their new song Pathos Y Lagrimas, off their debut album soon to be released on Mexican Summer.

data.title: Converse Ready, Set Get Lost: Citizens! "True Romance" Live
data.description: It was lashing rain in Brooklyn when we met up with English band Citizens!, as part of our Ready, Set Get Lost series, but the band powered through their set on the corner of N 10th and Wythe. Situated in North Williamsburg, we huddled from the rain as the band swept through a gorgeous rendition of "True Romance" in their weather appropriate Boots, which is out now on Kitsune.

data.title: Converse Rubber Tracks: Smokey Robotics records "Barefoot"
data.description:
Recorded at Converse Rubber Tracks, Smokey Robotic's single "Barefoot" is
this week's "Track of the Week". Watch the band collaborate in the
studio, work with the Converse Rubber Tracks engineer on the single and
record the original music, all while painter, Evan Smith, creates an
original work of art, in the studio that is inspired by the music being
made by the band.

data.title: Converse Rubber Tracks: Oh, Hello - Smokey Robotic Interview
data.description:
Meet the four members of Smokey Robotic: singer-songwriters Seer & Father
Dude and production duo, !llmind and Konrad OldMoney. Currently residing
in New York City, the band shares stories of their diverse backgrounds and
what not only inspired them to start making music but what influences them
today. Get to know the guys as they discuss how their collaborative
songwriting and production process unfolds in the studio and what it meant
to record at Converse Rubber Tracks as a band.
